    "privileged_info_summary": "Chemical safety limits for five hazard assessment scenarios: (1) Acetone at 12,000 ppm has LEL of 26,000 ppm and AEGL-3 60-min of 5,700 ppm, resulting in TOXIC status. (2) Methanol at 80,000 ppm has LEL of 55,000 ppm and AEGL-3 60-min of 7,200 ppm, resulting in TOXIC AND EXPLOSIVE status. (3) Chlorine at 100 ppm is non-flammable with AEGL-3 60-min of 20 ppm (not 50 ppm as claimed in metadata), resulting in TOXIC status. (4) Propane at 15,000 ppm has LEL of 21,000 ppm and AEGL-3 60-min of 33,000 ppm (not TEEL-3 21,000 ppm as claimed), resulting in SAFE status. (5) Propylene Oxide at 500 ppm has LEL of 28,000 ppm and AEGL-3 60-min of 870 ppm (not 750 ppm as claimed), resulting in SAFE status. Data sourced from CAMEO Chemicals (NOAA) and EPA AEGL Program, which are authoritative public sources for chemical safety information.",
